{{Infobox person | name = Andreas Herbst | birth_name = | image = | caption = | imagesize = | birth_date = 1955 | birth_place = [[Berlin]], [[Germany]] | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = [[Historian]] | language = |party = |parents = |alma_mater = | nationality = [[Germany|German]] | spouse = }}
'''Andreas Herbst''' (born [[Berlin]] 20 October 1955) is a [[Germany|German]] [[historian]].<ref name=BiographischeDatenbankenAH>{{cite web|url=http://www.bundesstiftung-aufarbeitung.de/wer-war-wer-in-der-ddr-%2363%3B-1424.html?Aut=AnH|author1= |author2= |title =Angaben zum Autor AnH|publisher= Bundesstiftung zur Aufarbeitung der SED-Diktatur: Biographische Datenbanken |accessdate= 7 February 2015}}</ref> His career has been divided between authorship and museum work. He has written extensively on aspects of the [[German Democratic Republic]] and since 2001 has worked for the (recently renovated) [[Memorial to the German Resistance|German Resistance Memorial Center]] in Berlin.<ref name=StiftGedeDeWiAH>{{cite web|url=http://www.gdw-berlin.de/de/gedenkstaette/struktur/|title=Gedenkstätte Deutscher Widerstand: Struktur |author=|publisher=[[Memorial to the German Resistance|Gedenkstätte Deutscher Widerstand]], Berlin|work=|date=|accessdate=7 February 2015}}</ref>
==Life and career== Herbst was born in the [[German Democratic Republic|German Democratic Republic (East Germany)]] and was almost 35 by the time (as officially identified) of [[German reunification]]. Between 1977 and 1982 he studied [[:de:Geschichtswissenschaft|Historical Sciences]] at Berlin's [[Humboldt University of Berlin|Humboldt University]]. After obtaining his degree he worked as a research assistant at the [[:de:Museum für Deutsche Geschichte|Museum for German History (''Museum für Deutsche Geschichte'')]] in Berlin. The museum celebrated the nation's history through the [[Historical materialism|Marxist prism]], as something driven by [[The Communist Manifesto|class struggle]]. In the context of the [[Die Wende|changes of 1989/90]] the [[Council of Ministers of the GDR|East German government]] decided to close it during 1990. Herbst moved on to work for the [[:de:Historische Kommission zu Berlin|Berlin Historical Commission]], now being transformed under the leadership of [[:de:Wolfram Fischer|Wolfram Fischer]].<ref>For biographical background see also Andreas Herbst, [[:de:Hermann Weber (Historiker, 1928)|Hermann Weber]]: ''Deutsche Kommunisten. Biographisches Handbuch 1918 bis 1945''. 2., Reworked and much extended edition 2008. Dietz, Berlin 2008, p. 1167, Section: "Anhang/Autoren" ''(Appendices: The authors)''.</ref>
In 1998 he took a job at the Centre for European Social Research at [[University of Mannheim|Mannheim University]].<ref name=BiographischeDatenbankenAH/> Since 2001 has worked for the [[Memorial to the German Resistance|German Resistance Memorial Center]] in Berlin, currently as the Exhibitions Organiser.<ref name=StiftGedeDeWiAH/>
